             and 
               
                  <persName id="t18310908-284-defend2065" type="defendantName">
                     JOHN 
                     ROBINSON
                  <interp inst="t18310908-284-defend2065" type="surname" value="ROBINSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-defend2065" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-defend2065" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-defend2065" type="age" value="13"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             were indicted for <rs id="t18310908-284-off1457" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-off1457" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-off1457" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18310908-284-cd1458" type="crimeDate">2nd of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-284-off1457 t18310908-284-cd1458"></join>, 1 silver spoon, value 7s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t18310908-284-victim2067" type="victimName">
                     Edward Pinder 
                     Lygon
                  <interp inst="t18310908-284-victim2067" type="surname" value="Lygon"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-victim2067" type="given" value="Edward Pinder"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-victim2067" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-284-off1457 t18310908-284-victim2067"></join>
                  </persName>
               
             and others.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-284-person2068">
                  THOMAS 
                  TURNER
               <interp inst="t18310908-284-person2068" type="surname" value="TURNER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-person2068" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-person2068" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am under-butler to <rs id="t18310908-284-viclabel1459" type="occupation">Colonel</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-284-victim2067 t18310908-284-viclabel1459"></join> Edward Pinder Lygon. This spoon was for the service of the whole regiment, and was in his care; I count the plate once a day - it was all right between one and two o'clock on the 2nd of August; I saw a boy down the area, at the kitchen door, between six and seven o'clock in the evening, but do not know who he was; Mason brought me the spoon next morning.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-284-person2069">
                  JOHN 
                  DICKSON
               <interp inst="t18310908-284-person2069" type="surname" value="DICKSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-person2069" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-person2069" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a shopman to Mr. Hunter, a silversmith, of Tottenham-court-road. On the 2nd of August, between seven and eight o'clock in the evening, I saw the prisoners loitering at our window, and heard one say to the other, "Break a piece off;" our shop door was open - Rohinson then brought the bowl of the spoon in to me, and asked if it was silver - I detained him, went out and brought Spiers in, and on him I found the other part of the spoon.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310908-284-person2070">
                  JOHN 
                  MASON
               <interp inst="t18310908-284-person2070" type="surname" value="MASON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-person2070" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-person2070" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoners in charge with the spoon.</p>
               <p>Spiers put in a written Defence, stating that Robinson asked him to go with him to sell something, and gave him part of the spoon to hold while he went to know what was the value of it.</p>
               <p>Robinson. I am sorry for having taken the spoon - I never was accused of any crime before.</p>
               <p>Robinson received a good character.</p>
               <p>ROBINSON - <rs id="t18310908-284-verdict1460" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-verdict1460" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 13.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18310908-284-punish1461" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-punish1461" type="punishmentCategory" value="corporal"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-punish1461" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="whipping"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-284-defend2065 t18310908-284-punish1461"></join>
               Whipped
            </rs>, and delivered to his Master.</p>
               <p>SPIERS - <rs id="t18310908-284-verdict1462" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310908-284-verdict1462" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               NOT GUILTY
